Perhaps we can change gcc to insert nops in front of lea so that the call is properly aligned for validation - not sure, needs investigation.

Switching optimizations off in the linker may be the right way to go only in short term, as it can lead to noticeable performance decrease.

Gnu2 tls does not validate as is - its mechanics is based on indirect call. I didn't investigate yet how to change it for validation while keeping its performance bonuses.
